SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within a couple of minutes of receiving the shot, my daughter felt hotness running down the length of her vaccinated arm and into her hand. Started feeling hot and started to produce a small patch of hives on the outside of the throat and chest. Did vigorous windmill motions with vaccinated arm.  She had a feeling of slight unwellness that was followed by a rush of energy.  As we leave the store and start to drive home her hives are a little bit worse and she says she feels a little lightheaded and has some heart palpations. But is still reporting a rush of energy. By the time we get home 10 minutes later hives,  lightheadedness, and heart palpations have resolved.  She feels great the rest of the day. Next day slight redness around the injection site and arm a bit sore. The following day redness is gone but a slight rash is starting to show up around the neck. 5 days later, the rash becomes inflamed, sore, hot and itchy, hives are full upper-body flareups. She takes Allegra 24 for hives control. Rash comes and goes daily.  Acts more like hives. Allegra 24 controls hives mostly along with icing. After a few days, the effectiveness of the Allegra 24 is not as efficient with the neck rash. Switches to Zyrtec 24 which seems to provide better relief from both hives and rash around the neck. Sees Dr. April 29th. He advises not to take a second dose of Pfizer at this time and prescribes her an EpiPen.
LAB_DATA: Has had blood drawn but has not received results from the blood work at this time. Dr. will also be sending her to an allergist at a future date.
OTHER_MEDS: None, she did not take her usual vitamins the day of the vaccine.
PRIOR_VAX: She was maybe 4-5 years old. Painful large welt and inflammation around the vaccine site aproximately the size of an adult hand

The patient previously received her first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, lot number: EL8982) at the age of 88-years-old, via an unspecified route of administration in right deltoid on 29Jan2021 at 0.3 mL, single for COVID-19 immunization. The patient was calling about the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine and mentioned that she had a reaction but didn't think it was from the vaccine because it was 5 weeks to the date after the second shot. The reaction was very severe, and she had to visit the emergency room. The patient experienced throat closing, tongue swelling, face swelling and a hard time breathing. She saw her primary care provider after that, and she also saw her PMR doctor- physical medicine and rehabilitation. The doctors recommended that she report this reaction to the COVID 19 vaccine five weeks later. Both doctors thought it might be from the vaccine and it was worth reporting. When asked about the symptoms and if they occurred at that same time, the patient stated yes, and they diagnosed her symptoms as angioedema in the emergency room. This happened on 26Mar2021. The patient was never admitted to the hospital. When asked if angioedema improved, worsened or was persisting, patient stated it was nonexistent now. The events happened after the second dose of the vaccine. The patient had to stop her medications because her primary care provider was unsure what may have caused this reaction, but it may be her medications. She has been taking losartan potassium for about ten years but now had to stop because angioedema could possibly be the result of that, even after ten years. She also had to stop diclofenac sodium because they may have caused that kind of reaction. Having to stop ibuprofen broke her heart as she has taken it for years. This too could have that type of reaction. For aflibercept, she mentioned that she gets the injections in both eyes every eight weeks. She had it 31 times in the right eye and 30 times in the left eye. The reaction she was speaking of, the emergency room, came exactly 2 weeks after she had her last injections, which was on 11Mar2021. Angioedema was an emergency situation, if the throat closes and they couldn't open it up, they may cut into the neck and windpipe. The description was enough to scare her. Both doctors suggested the Pfizer vaccine as just possibly a late reaction. The patient had a basic metabolic panel while in the emergency room. She reported that potassium and sodium was low. Chest Xray- the patient did not have a report on it. Nasal scan was fine. COVID nasal test was negative. Swab for many other kinds of viruses was negative. All of these tests were done on 26Mar2021. The last several days I have been experiencing strong pain, achy ness  and the muscle weakness in my elbows through my hands.  I have also felt the same ache in my shoulders and knees the last several days as well.  But the arm one is significant.  It is hard to hold anything for a long period of time.  NSAIDs do not seem to make much of a difference at all.  I don?t know if it?s related but it?s the only other time I have felt this way before.  I did nothing physical to warrant my issues.  I just figured I would report this in case I am not alone.
PRIOR_VAX: Moderna Covid 19

SYMPTOM_TEXT: it could have been a seizure; Unconscious/Collapsed/ diagnosed her as having a Syncopal Episode; Urinated on self/Wet her pants; Headaches; Feeling light headed; Felt her heart beat faster; Sore arm; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable nurse (patient mother). A 45-year-old female patient received bnt162b2 (BNT162B2, lot number EW0150 and expiration date was not provided), via an unspecified route of administration first dose on 05Apr2021 15:00 at single dose for covid-19 immunisation. The patient's medical history included ongoing Hypertension (Patient diagnosed in her late 30's), ongoing Hypothyroid (Patient diagnosed when she was around 20 years old), ongoing Allergies, ongoing Gastrooesophageal reflux disease (The patient was exposed to a chemical in her 20's that caused this condition), ongoing Birth control, ongoing Allergic to eggs (States patient has never received the flu vaccine due to her egg allergy), and ongoing Allergic to shellfish. The patient's concomitant medications included ongoing levothyroxine at 150 ug, 1x/day for Hypothyroid, ongoing Hydrochlorothiazide at 12.5 mg, 1x/day for hypertension, ongoing omeprazole at 20 mg, 1x/day for gastrooesophageal reflux disease, ongoing losartan at 100 mg, 1x/day for hypertension, ongoing norethisterone (SHAROBEL) for Birth control. On 06Apr2021 13:00, the reporter stated that her daughter fainted at work, lost her urine, and was unconscious and was taken to the Emergency Room. Primary Care Physician told her daughter she should have no problem getting the second vaccine. States that she was not certain if her daughter should get the second shot. It was scheduled for next week. Also, reported that after lunch reporter stated that her daughter fainted in her office at work. She had urinated on herself and was unconscious. Caller was concerned it could have been a seizure. Her daughter was taken to the Emergency Room and they diagnosed her as having a Syncopal Episode. On 06Apr2021, the patient had headaches that continue since these events. The reporter stated that her daughter's doctor told her daughter that the blood work and electrocardiogram done at the Emergency Room were normal. The Emergency Room and her daughter's doctor acted like her symptoms were not serious. The reporter looked at the Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System website and it said that a syncopal episode is a reportable event. Says that her daughter's doctors did not report this event. Says doctors need to have training on the importance of reporting events. The reporter called the Food and Drug Administration last week but she hasn't heard anything from them. States they told her it could take 5-7 business days. Says she called Pfizer today to see if there was any further information or guidance she could get as she is concerned about her daughter. She says her daughter has her own office so she was in there alone when she collapsed. Someone found her on the floor. The reporter was asking for guidance on administration of the second vaccine dose following a syncopal episode after the first. The patient received her first vaccine dose on 05Apr2021 15:00 and she was fine, she had a sore arm, but went to work the next day (06Apr2021) and after lunch she reported feeling light headed and felt her heart beat faster and went to get up and a colleague later found her on the floor and she had wet her pants. They took her to the ER around 1 pm the day after her vaccination and diagnosed her with a syncopal episode stating that they didn't think it was from the shot. The events syncope, urinary incontinence, seizure, and headache were considered as serious (medically significant) by the reporter. The events syncope, and urinary incontinence caused emergency room visit and physician office visit. The outcome of the events syncope, urinary incontinence was recovered on 06Apr2021.  The outcome of the event Headache was not recovered. The outcome of the remaining events was unknown.; Sender's Comments: Based on the information currently available, a causal association between the reported events and bnt162b2 cannot be fully excluded.Case will be reassessed when additional information is available. SYMPTOM_TEXT: bent over to look up and almost blacked out; swimmy headedness was really more noticeable after second shot; sensation in equilibrium or vision or whatever; weakness; felt different/really knew something was wrong/something is not right; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). An 85-year-old male patient received the second dose of bnt162b2, via an unspecified route of administration, administered in Left arm on 09Feb2021 (Lot Number: EM9810) as single dose for covid-19 immunisation. The patient medical history and concomitant medications were not reported. The patient previously received the first dose of bnt162b2, at the age of 85-year-old, via an unspecified route of administration, administered in Left arm on 20Jan2021 (lot number: EL3302) as single dose for covid-19 immunization and experienced Vertigo, felt peculiar, nausea, dizziness/swimmy headed. The patient previously received the flu shot for immunization and experienced Sore arm. He is 85 and not familiar with all the goings on today but heard a report the other day and did not know there was such a thing as Vertigo. He thought that was just a movie. When he took the shot at (place name) in (county name) on 20Jan2021, soon thereafter, not that day but maybe next, he felt peculiar. It was just uneasiness and he did not feel right. That went on and on 09Feb2021, he got second shot and he got swimmy headed, but it has continued on since then and probably gotten worse, especially when he gets up in the morning. He has to hold on until he gets balanced or coordinated. It just doesn't seem right After he gets up and gets going, it is not as prevalent. But then sometimes it strikes him and he is just completely out of it. He later stated the peculiar feeling and swimmy headedness started the same day as the first injection, but he just did not really pay attention to it and thought it was just one of those things that you accept with getting older. Wife and he both went and he thought his feelings were merely from excitement or depletion or exhaustion. He felt like he had weakness and he just felt different. He got it at noon and waited for 15 minutes. Because of the events around him at the time, it did not register with him because it was the stress of driving 30 miles through expressway. Old people aren't used to driving that far. It got worse after the second shot and then he really knew something was wrong. When you are old, you have these feelings and pains and aches and all that stuff, and you just accept it as being old. It did not register with him until a couple of weeks ago when he heard it on TV about Vertigo and he said that is what he has. The swimmy headedness was really more noticeable after second shot, it brought it on stronger. He does not complain about things and thought it may just be getting old. He said it just kept on and getting a little worse and worse. Then he said something is not right and one day he bent over to look up and almost blacked out because of sensation in equilibrium or vision or whatever. He got scared and that was a couple of weeks ago. (name) was not cognizant of what was going on until he heard on television about Vertigo. One of the news channel mentioned or somebody mentioned it. It was just general things. He confirmed it was regarding someone who had gotten Vertigo after getting the vaccine but did not have a particular person to report on. NO ER or physician's office required. The outcome of the event dizziness aggravated and Weakness was not recovered, other events was unknown.

The patient's medical history was not reported. Concomitant medication included betamethasone dipropionate, ketoconazole (KETO B). The caller reported that after receiving her first dose of Pfizer-Biontech covid19 vaccine on 10Apr2021 she had symptoms. Later that night her heart rate accelerated. She experienced chest pains and her blood pressure went up. She went to the urgent care and had an EKG. The result was normal with no abnormal findings. She reported increase heart rate latest for 4 days. The chest pain lasted for 5-6 days. She did not have a primary care provider. She was going to get her blood pressure checked today. On 15Apr2021, she reported that her blood pressure was elevated to 135/90 mmHg, which was abnormal for her and blood pressure went up. She asked whether she should she continue with the second dose. She had a side effect after the first dose of the vaccine. It was 135/90 at the Urgent Care. She was asking if she should move forward to get the second dose or stay with the one. She was not sure how it would effect her later on and she wanted to be safe. She asked whether she would experience harmful effects if she did not get the 2 doses of the vaccine. She received a response stating that there were no reports of increased heart rate or blood pressure during clinical trials. Further she received a response from HCP that stated as noted in the Fact Sheet for Recipients, she should not get the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine if she had a severe allergic reaction after a previous dose of the vaccine or if she had a severe allergic reaction to any ingredient of the vaccine. The decision to receive the second dose for any other reason cannot be made by Pfizer. They referred her to speak to her healthcare provider about the risks of the vaccine compared to the risks of potentially not being fully protected against COVID-19 infection. Her healthcare provider knows her health situation and has access to information that can better help inform this decision. The patient reported AEs after receiving her first dose of Pfizer-Biontech covid19 vaccine on 10Apr2021. She wanted to know if she is at risk of any additional adverse events, if she were to only get one dose. She received a response which stated that the commonly reported AEs were reported after both the first and second doses.  Efficacy was determined 7 days after the second dose was given, no data on how well patients are protected by just one dose. Not aware of other risks for getting only one dose of vaccine instead of the recommended two. The patient did not receive additional vaccines administered on same date of the Pfizer Suspect. The patient did not receive any other vaccines within 4 weeks prior to the COVID vaccine. In addition,  I  had GI issues (lots of loose stools and some cramping) within the first six hours of taking the first dose. Those symptoms went away fairly soon, but when I ate dried cranberries again the same thing occurred so I think that might have been the issue. Around April 11th, I almost passed out twice in the night when I got up to go to the bathroom and I did not feel very good. I was in an office two days before where the staff had been fully vaccinated, but two of the staff were not wearing masks and I overheard one of them saying they had not been feeling good. I felt fine on the date of my second vaccine on April 20th so I went in for my shot.  Right after my first shot I felt fine. However, about eight to 10 hours later, I started running a temperature,  had chills, terrible muscle aches, felt terrible  generally, and started having ringing in my ears. All of my symptoms got much worse and I am sure my fever was at least 102 , but I never took it until my chills were better and at that point it was 101. I then took 500 mg of Tylenol and within about three hours my fever was reduced to 99. In about 30 hours, my fever was gone and I felt better, but was still very tired and had ringing in my ears. It has been almost two weeks since my second shot and I still have ringing in my ears and it is worse when I am lying down or am quite. I am also a little more tired than usual and my insomnia is worse than usual. My main concern is the ringing in my ears.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Unspecified Cardiac Event; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (Patient's Daughter). A 60-year-old female patient received first dose of bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 mRNA VACCINE, Solution for injection, Lot number: EK4176), via an unspecified route of administration on 15Jan2021 at single dose for COVID-19 immunization. The patient also received second dose of bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 mRNA VACCINE, Solution for injection, Lot number: EK4176), via an unspecified route of administration on 05Feb2021 at single dose for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included chronic obstructive pulmonary disease from an unknown date to 21Feb2021, brain aneurysm, smoker. Family medical history included States her Grandfather had skin cancer, but it was benign, moles and then freeze them off. No cardiac events. Grandma passed away infection from knee surgery. The patient received a Prior Vaccinations within 4 weeks has received both doses of the Pfizer Covid Vaccine. Concomitant medication was not reported. On 21Feb2021, patient experienced unspecified cardiac event. Caller stated that she was calling in regards to her mother regarding the Covid19 vaccine. States she was instructed by the pathologist to call Pfizer directly, rather than just report on VAERS. States this was not the same pathologist as the one that did the autopsy. Caller states does have a copy of the autopsy. States she called several pathologist to get the autopsy done. Dr. called her back after it had been done, and the caller discussed with him, the patient passed away after some cardiac event. States it is not clear what cardiac event. States she passed away 16 days after receiving her second dose of the vaccine. States the patient's physician would be happy to talk to Pfizer about it. Reporter states her mom was an LPN there and they all know her. States anyone there is fully aware of who she is. States some people in the office are taking it hard, and they may get sentimental. States it helps if people get things business and not talk about feelings. Reporter states it was 8:50am when the EMTs arrived and she had already passed. Caller states was who did the autopsy. She has been speaking with a lady, but she goes by (university name). States (Hospital Name) is a hospital, it used to be (University name). Hospital. Reporter states (phone number) is a direct line to (university name). Reporter states when the autopsy results came back she had the original and they are sending another because of the cause of death. Reporter states the autopsy showed no Pulmonary Obstruction, which made them question, well did she have COPD? States it was interesting because her mom was a smoker but her lungs were pink, and there was no fluid or obstruction in her lungs. States her mom taught her a little bit growing up. Reporter states she was going to be a nurse too but she lost her grant because she got married, now she doesn't qualify. Caller stats an autopsy was done; however they did not do a toxicology report. Caller states that patient was an organ donor. States she received a letter from them stating the patient will be helping a lot of people with skin grafts. Reporter adds, the patient was negative for Covid, she had to be tested for the autopsy. States she died from some type of cardiac event. States the patient did have COPD but on the autopsy, her lungs were clear and there were no pulmonary obstructions. States the liver showed possible hypertension, but the patient did not have hypertension. Reporter states there are some interesting things with her autopsy report and the patient's PCP could go over it medically if necessary. Reporter states this morning she saw several articles that state heart inflammation has been linked to the vaccine. Caller asks if she still needs to report it through VAERS? States she should have done it in the beginning but her mom was a big supporter of the vaccine. Reporter states her mom was on Facebook, and someone stated they weren't sure about getting the vaccine and her mom had commented, well she just got her second one, let's see what happens and then she died 16 days later. States that is why she was hesitated to report it. States the Pathologist encouraged her to call in and report it. Caller states she does not know if her mom had any other adverse events. States she will not say a word about things unless it gets really bad. Reporter states the only person that would know is Dr. meant a lot to her mom and she would be willing to tell her doctor, but not her daughter because she wouldn't want her to worry. Caller states the patient never used her inhaler, it is still full. States she took her mom's purse because her mom lived out of her purse, everything she needed was in there. Reporter states the patient had Tylenol, Sudafed, Advil, and Prednisone in her purse. Reporter states she knows she wasn't taking Prednisone. States the pill box is locked and it looks like it hasn't been open in a while. Reporter states she does not know if she was taking any medication, Dr. may have more information. Reporter states no, she didn't go to the doctor or the ER. States the patient's dog woke up her stepdad and she had already passed away. States they have her dog and he is going through a lot, when she first passed the dog had aggressive tendencies, and when she would lay with him, he would nudge her to get up. He doesn't like it when people go to sleep and that makes it harder. States the dog ended up getting an eye infection, because his tear ducts were clogged, states he did that a couple weeks, and now he is getting better, not as fearful or aggressive. Reporter states when her mom had the brain aneurysm, it takes a little bit longer for anesthesia to wear off. States it was an extremely strong anesthesia that she had never had before. States she wouldn't let anyone take care of her except for her. States when she was under anesthesia, she would call her mom. States they would know when she said mom, she was talking about her daughter. States her mom said she looks like her grandma when she was younger. Consumer adds the patient's husband's contact information, in case it is needed. On 21Feb2021, the patient died due to cardiac event secondary to COPD. Autopsy was perfomed. Autopsy details was available. The outcome of the event was fatal.; Reported Cause(s) of Death: Cardiac Event Secondary to COPD
LAB_DATA: Test Name: Covid; Test Result: Negative

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within minutes of getting administered the shot, my entire body started to sweat, and I got very intense nausea and period cramps that was 8/10 on pain scale. I was moaning and crying and didn't know what to do. After they came to check on me about 15 minutes later, I asked if I could take Advil and they said I could so I did. I also told them I felt like I was going to throw up, so they gave me this bin, and I threw up twice.  I was supposed to get my period later that day or the next day, but it hadn't started yet and I felt completely fine when I first got there before I got the shot. But it was almost instantaneous after the shot that I had the sweating, nausea, and period cramps that made me feel like I couldn't walk or talk because I was in so much pain. I kept wanting to be crouched down and also to have my head down. The nurse kept asking me what I needed, and I didn't know, I just kept saying, "I don't feel good, I don't feel good." I eventually asked to go to the bathroom because I thought that might help even though I didn't actually have to go. They took me to the bathroom where I kept moaning and crying and felt so awful. Only a couple times did the pain subside for about 5 seconds but then came right back. I think it was probably an hour of this when they called the paramedics to take me to the emergency room. But as soon as they arrived to the women's bathroom in the mall where we were, the pain finally subsided. They still wanted to take me to the ER, but I convinced them not to because I was feeling better and worried about the bill I would receive and dealing with all the insurance stuff. They eventually agreed to let me stay in my car 30 more minutes while being monitored. The nurses were all very nice and gave me juice and snacks to help the nausea, and then they scheduled my next appointment at the hospital and told me I should come with someone next time. When I got home I noticed my arm was sore, but I knew that was normal so wasn't too worried about it. However it's now been sore almost three weeks, and I can't move it certain directions, which is super frustrating because I've been pursuing dance outside of my day job and hadn't gotten an injury from that all year, but now all of a sudden I can't move my arm a lot of ways and it's affected me being able to take class and do choreography, and also regular household things. I can't reach with my left arm to grab things, and I can't ever tense the muscle in my upper left arm / shoulder, and if it tenses by accident (i.e. I go to grab something that's falling or see a bug), pain shoots through. And now I have read about vaccines causing shoulder injuries, and I'm feeling quite frustrated, which is what led me to find this vaccine report site, and is why I am probably going to cancel my second dose appointment.

About 12 hours post-vaccine, I began feeling ill with chills and night sweats (but no temperature). After a night of fitful sleeping, I awoke the next morning feeling under the weather. I took Tylenol early that morning (around 8 a.m.). Subsequently, I took a nap at 10:45 a.m. and awoke around 3:30 p.m. with a very high temperature of 103.9. I took Tylenol immediately and my temperature rose to 104.2 (measured by head-scanning thermometer) within 15-30 minutes. I was dizzy, nauseated, almost unable to walk or sit up straight, and frankly was the sickest I have ever been in my life. I took a cold shower sitting down and within an hour my temperature had dropped to 101. I slowly began to feel better over the next 2-3 days, with symptoms lessening quickly that evening. I would absolutely take the vaccine over again, but wish that I had been advised that a very high temperature could occur in a very small subset of people. All the literature from the vaccine site and other government institutions did not note the possibility of a temperature of 103 - 104 degrees.
LAB_DATA: None - was scared to go the hospital/urgent care where I might be put in a waiting room with COVID-positive patients or where I could be exposed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 24-36 hours after receiving my second dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine I started having three noticeable side effects: pronounced exhaustion, occasional mild headaches, and a transient heart arrhythmia usually lasting 5-15 seconds.  These symptoms have not subsided and the arrhythmia became persistent enough last night that it required a trip to the local ER. The first doctor I spoke to, informed me that he had been out of work for a week following his second dose of the Pfizer vaccine due to transient, but consistent, heart palpitations, which ultimately brought him into the ER to take his own EKG. He advised me that a number of other patients with identical complaints had come to the ER over the last 4-5 weeks. Ultimately he referred me to a local cardiologist and told me not to worry about the arrhythmia, that it would clear up in a few days. I?m curious why this isn?t listed as a common side effect of the vaccine, had it been, I would not have been so concerned about it.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The evening after I got the shot my arms/elbows were very itchy.  The next morning, I had red circles/small "welts" on my forearms and elbows.  They were very itchy.
LAB_DATA: I went to an urgent care location; the doctor said I had hives that were probably from the vaccine.  He prescribed Prednisone and Pepcid.  These medications helped, but once I went off them, the hives came back even worse (basically all over my body; they would come and go sporadically).  I then went to a Dermatologist who confirmed they were hives and said she was certain they were from the vaccine.  She put me on Allegra (morning) and Zyrtec (evening), doubling the dose of each as well as prescribed Triamcinolone Acetonide Cream.  The cream didn't really help, nor did the allergy medicine.  I then went to my GP's office; the doctor told me to try Benadryl at night instead of the Zyrtec.  That didn't do anything different.  This was all before my second dose.
OTHER_MEDS: Fish Oil, calcium supplement, probiotic, mult-vitamin

Burning began in the center of my chest that increased in area and intensity.  It spread to my back and the pain became a level 9.  I was taken to the ER and treated for suspected heart attack.  The diagnosis was finally made at esophagitis.  I spent 5 days in that hospital.  Three days later I experienced severe heart palpitations that caused dizziness for two hours to such a degree that I could not stand up.  Over the course of the next six weeks, I continued to have daily episodic attacks of this nature with a lessening degree of symptoms each time.  As of today, the symptoms have not recurred.  Additionally, I began to experience significant hair loss at the same time as the onset of the other symptoms to such a degree that when brushing my hair I would get a fistful of it in my brush.  The hair loss has slowly diminished, and as of today, the excessive hair loss has ceased.

This is a 76-year-old male with dementia who is well cared for at home by his wife who brought him in the the ER on 4/16/21 for  for altered mental status and not acting right.  Patient is wife states he had his second Moderna Covid vaccine 2 weeks ago and has been declining steadily ever since.  She notes he has had brain "fog" with increased confusion weakness and fatigue where he is no longer doing his baseline activities.  She has noticed him getting more winded and tired with routine activity and then sleeps a lot.  she feels like his dementia suddenly went on a rapid escalation.  The morning of his ER visit her concern was he was acting as if his blood sugar was low described him as being sweaty, he was shaking, he was very weak and lethargic.  She noted his temp at that point was 92.5 his blood pressure was 139/70 his heart rate was 70 and his blood sugar sugar was over 200.  Patient also has a history of diabetes  in addition to the dementia and he had a history of alcohol use disorder until 4 years ago when he suddenly stopped drinking. Her main concern was the rapid change since his Covid vaccine and now he is not sleeping at night and he is sleeping more significantly during the day and she is nearing exhaustion at this point. She saw the PCP and they said there is nothing they can do and told her to bring him to the ER
LAB_DATA: Labs reviewed with patient's wife there is no specific correctable etiology to attribute his significant decline at this time Patient is obviously requiring more care from his wife she does not have a neurologist or geriatrician at this point and prefers to stay locally.  Called  Dr.  for neurology in and discussed further treatment options and pt was prescribed 25 mg of Seroquel at bedtime to help regulate his sleep and see if this causes some significant improvement.  Pt to follow up with neurology.  Patient was also negative for Covid Results of MRI discussed with the wife radiologist suggests nonspecific dilation of his ventricles in relation to the degree of atrophy could consider normal pressure hydrocephalus.  However gait disturbance is not a primary symptom at this point as well as incontinence which has been occasional in the past. MRI brain 1.  No acute intracranial abnormality. 2.  The ventricles are enlarged, disproportionate to the degree of cortical atrophy. Findings are non-specific, however may be seen in normal pressure hydrocephalus in the correct clinical setting. 3.  There is a tiny extra-axial lesion at the vertex of the skull, which appears to demonstrate enhancement and may represent a tiny meningioma.

Wednesday, April 28: 10 days after COVID Shot 1: area where the shot was started getting dark pink/red, with burning/itching feelings in arm, and pain in arm, also pain in left leg by my varicose veins shooting downward. Exhaustion sets in.  Thursday, April 29: leg pain is gone. Arm the same, area where the shot was starts getting dark pink/red, with burning/itching feelings in arm. Pain in arm is gone. I had hives since getting the first dose that hadn't gone away.  After getting my second dose, I still had the hives and I woke up in the middle of the night and they had spread; I had them on my upper legs, my butt, my stomach, my back, my arms....  I went back to bed and managed to fall asleep.  I was then woken up by my husband who informed me that my eyes were a little swollen and my lips were quite swollen.  I had been told when I got my second dose to go to the ER if I had any swelling on my face, so my husband drove me to the ER.  They admitted me and gave me Prednisone, Pepcid and Benadryl intravenously; I was at the ER for about five hours before I was sent home with a nine day prescription for Prednisone and a prescription for an Epi-Pen; the doctor also told me to take one or two Benadryl every six hours for 24 hours.  Two days later I had an appointment with an allergist who told me to start taking two Allegra in the morning and two Zyrtec in the evening.  She also prescribed me Doxepin to help me sleep (I hadn't been sleeping well because the itching was keeping me awake).  Two days after that I had a follow-up appointment with my GP.  She was on board with everything the allergist said.
LAB_DATA: I have had various blood tests done over the past six weeks.  All results came back normal.

I received my second Moderna vaccine at 10:00am on 4/13, 28 days after my first one. On Fri, 4/16 at 4:00am, I woke up to use the restroom and voided my bladder. Shortly thereafter, I felt very nauseous and cold clammy. I had a sip of water, than sat down next the toilet since I thought I had food poisoning and needed to throw up. Instead, I passed out and fell from a sitting position against the wall. I woke up a few seconds later, to find my right ear cut and with quite a bit of blood (not sure what I cut it on, maybe my own thumb nail?). I stood up and walked to the sink, so I could bleed over it while apply pressure so I wouldn't make a mess. My wife had woken up at this point, and shortly after I got to the sink, I passed out again while standing (fortunately she caught me) and started twitching for a few seconds before coming to (I came to while still standing up). At this point, my wife drove me to the emergency room and we were admitted. In the ER from 4:15am-7am, they did a CT scan on my head without contracts, blood work, and an EKG. All three tests came back normal and I was diagnosed with vasovagal syncope. I have no history of any prior vasovagal event. At the ER they also sewed my ear up with 6 dissolvable stitches, gave me a big of IV fluids, a tetanus shot, and then sent me on my way, discharging me at 7:00am on 4/16. I then saw my primary care doctor that afternoon at 1:00pm on 4/16 who reviewed by medical records/test results from the ER, concurred with their vasovagal syncope diagnosis, checked my stitches, and said I could go back to normal activity largely unrestricted. I haven't had any issues since; so not overly concerned (other than the >$2,500 of ER hospital bills that are piling up), but just reporting this so you have the data.
LAB_DATA: 4/16: EKG - normal; 4/16: Blood work - normal; 4/16: Head CT scan without contrast - normal
HISTORY: Was diagnosed with minor mitral valve prolapse 16 years ago with occasional benign heart palpitations at the time and received a recommendation to stay hydrated.  I haven't had a heart palpitation or any other symptoms in over 7 years and my EKG at my annual physical is always normal.
ALLERGIES: Minor allergy to dust and ragweed (treated with Allegra as needed, but hadn't taken any the week prior to the incident)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1 Week after vaccination I began seeing small red spots on my hands and feet that were initially mistaken for mosquito/small bug bites. By the next morning the red spots had spread significantly but still remained isolated to both hands and feet. The spots flattened and many appeared to be white in the center with red outlines. Both hands and feet began to swell and the redness became more concentrated with time, with some spots radiating up the arms and legs. I visited the doctor a little less than 48 hours after the reaction started. The doctor determined it was likely not other illnesses that it resembled (hand/foot/mouth disease, coxsackie virus, etc.). The red spots itched but not unbearably and the rash was mildly painful - sore and difficult to move hands and feet since the rash and swelling occurred on palms and bottom of feet. The doctor prescribed Prednisone for 5 days and the rash has began to lesson after 3 days, with the hands beginning to appear normal before the feet. The spots never opened, scabbed, or produced puss. No other symptoms such as fever, headache, sore throat, etc. No rash or symptoms at injection site.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received his vaccine and a few minutes later felt like he was going to pass out. He said his head felt  foggy and just didn't fell well. He was brought back to med observation 1 by wheelchair. He looked pale and felt clammy. We laid him down on the stretcher and almost immediately felt better. He had a water when he came to us and he was given some crackers to eat. His color returned to normal and skin felt warmer. He stated that he was ready to leave. His wife was out in the car waiting for him. We took vitals at 10:12 am - heart rate 79, o2 98, BP 115/83, at 10:16 am heart rate 80, o2 99, BP 125/79, at 10:20 am heart rate 80, o2 99, BP 127/76. We released patients with other at 10:21am.

At 0947, patient reported headache rated 5/10 on the pain scale and chest pain radiating to left shoulder (patient received vaccine on left arm). EMT assessed patient vitals: blood pressure 158/90 mmHg, heart rate regular 69 beats/minute, and SpO2 96%. Patient denied difficulty breathing, difficulty swallowing, itchiness, hives and rashes. Patient reported history of atrial fibrillation, pulmonary embolism, and surgeries on elbows, ankles and esophagus. Patient denied taking current medications. Patient offered 911. Patient declined 911. Patient given water and advised to wait for further observation. Patient reassessed at 1005. Patient vitals were blood pressure 149/90 mmHg, heart rate 67 beats/minute, and SpO2 97%. Patient reported headache decreased to 2/10 on the pain scale. Patient reassessed at 1015. Patient vitals were blood pressure 144/88 mmHg, heart rate 65 beats/minute, and SpO2 97%. Patient stated his headache was gone and he felt fine. Lead nurse educated patient on communicating with primary care provider about his reactions to the vaccine and seeking emergency care if symptoms worsen or has difficulty swallowing/breathing. At 1018, patient left facility to self with steady gait and unlabored breathing.
HISTORY: a-fib, pulmonary embolism, surgeries on ankles, wrists, elbows, and esophagus
PRIOR_VAX: pt reported  a similar reaction to his first dose when he was in the observation area

Client received the second Pfizer vaccine with lot number EW0161 exp. 7.31.21 at 11:26am. Client walked over to the EMT station from observation area and requested that his blood pressure be taken to EMT. Client stated that he was feeling "dizzy" but denied any pain throughout his body. Client appeared alert and tracking with his eyes, and in no apparent distress. Client stated that he had just finished his 15 minutes observation but began to feel dizzy after standing up prompting him to check in with the EMT station. This was the client's second dose of the Pfizer vaccine and he denied any significant reaction to the first dose. Client denied any underlying medical conditions, had no known allergies and is not on any medications. Client was negative for hives, redness, discoloration, severe sweating, shortness of breath or other signs of anaphylaxis. Client?s airway, breathing and circulation was intact and he was alert and oriented to person, place, date and event. Client stated that he did not eat breakfast or have very much water today. Vital signs at 1150 were: Blood pressure 120/88, Pulse - 72, O2 sat 97%, Respirations 16, eyes equal and reactive to light. Client consented to remaining an additional 30 minutes after his vital signs were measured. Client was provided with a snack and water to eat while completing his observation. Client's vitals remained stable and consistent throughout his observation. Vital signs at 1205 -blood pressure 124/88, heart rate 76, respiratory rate of 16, and oxygen saturation of 97% on room air. Vital signs at 1220 - blood pressure of 128/88, heart rate of 68, respiratory rate of 16, and oxygen saturation of 98% on room air. After the completion of his observation at 1220, client denied any further dizziness. No medications were indicated or administered and EMS was declined. Client was encouraged to seek medical care if their symptoms returned or increased later in the evening. Client departed  vaccination site at 1221 in confident disposition and stating he felt comfortable driving home.

At 1312 client verbalized to EMT was experiencing light-headedness after receiving her first dose of the Pizer vaccine. Client was then assisted by EMT and vaccinator to lay down on the gravity bed at EMT station. Translator was called over to help communicate to client, who is Spanish speaking. Client's airway remained patent and client appeared pink/warm and skin dry. Client denied any nausea or vomiting. Client stated that she felt anxious and was light-headed. EMT took the first set of vitals from client manually, and subsequent vitals were taken from wrist cuff. Vital signs at 1312 were: blood pressure of 138/92, pulse of 70, pulse oximetry of 98% on room air with round equal and reactive pupils, remaining alert and oriented to person, place and time. Client then reported having a history of hypertension along with mild allergic reaction to peanuts and shellfish, which resulted in full body rash and some respiratory difficulties. Client also reports taking 16 mg hydrochlorothiazide, for hypertension. Client was then monitored for 30 minutes sand vitals were taken every 5 mins. Vital signs at 1319 were: blood pressure of 141/87, pulse of 79, pulse oximetry of 98% on room air with round, equal and reactive pupils remaining alert and oriented to person, place and time. Vital signs at 1324 were: blood pressure of 140/80, pulse of 78, pulse oximetry of 98% on room air. Vital signs at 1328 were: blood pressure of 132/80, pulse of 81, pulse oximetry of 98% on room air. Vital signs at 1333 were: blood pressure of 134/82, pulse of 79, pulse oximetry of 99% on room air. Vital signs at 1338 were: blood pressure of 129/80, pulse of 68, pulse oximetry of 99% on room air. After 30 minutes, client again stated that she felt fine and that she was just anxious about getting the vaccine. Client's vital signs were within normal levels for client. No medications were administered to client and EMS was refused by client. Client was given information about what to monitor and was instructed to seek medical help if symptoms worsened after leaving. Client ambulated to car which was driven by a relative at 1345.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was very ill on Friday night after receiving the vaccination. Flu-like symptoms, high fever, shortness of breath, pain in my abdomen, horrible headache, nausea, dizziness, loss of consciousness and leg pain (both legs). The flu-like symptoms passed on Saturday, but by Tuesday, April 13 I was continuing to have a terrible headache, abdominal pain and leg pain. I saw my primary doctor on the 13th and was sent over to the hospital for an ultrasound of my leg. No clots were found and I was told to continue trying to recover at home unless it got worse. I was seen at the emergency room on April 14th for abdominal pain, leg pain, dizziness and headache. The nurse told me I was probably hysterical over the vaccination being pulled, and I told him this was not the case. They performed CT (without contrast) on my abdomen and head, then released me with instructions to return if I was worse. By the 16th I was unable to walk as my left side was completely numb. I went back to the ER. I had a CT of my abdomen and head with and without contrast. I had a lumbar puncture and several labs. I was given IV antibiotics for some infection they found in my urine. I was given fluids and pain meds, and my BP was shooting up to 145/94 (which is very high for me), when standing. My vision was blurry and I was unable to remember much of the last week. I was admitted from the 16th through the 20th and had an MRV, 2 MRIs, more lab work and medicine for my headache. I was released on the 20th and the headache was unbearable and I was still numb on my left side, going back to my doctor on the 22nd. He suggested the ER, and the ER admitted me back to the stroke unit. I was released on the 22nd with a diagnosis of a hemiplegic migraine that could cause stroke-like symptoms (ZERO history of headaches previously). I was sent home with a walker and home health services. PT visited on April 30th and ordered two visits per week for the next month. I am unable to walk without a walker. I cannot shower or use the stairs without assistance. My memory is still foggy. I am unable to concentrate for long. I often stutter and can't remember basic words. I have also stopped and forgotten where I am at a given moment. I am on Depakote nightly for the headaches, and they have lessened slightly, but when they flare up it is debilitating and I often vomit. I have instructions to follow up with my primary tomorrow morning and see what the next steps are.
LAB_DATA: All CTs, scans, MRV and MRI were normal. I am unaware of lab results. The infection in my urine wasn't discussed with me until after they started me on IV antibiotics.  PT assessment was that I am just barely able to be left alone and not in a rehab facility.
OTHER_MEDS: Spirulina (sporadic) Estradiol estrogen patch 0.05mg (twice weekly) Citalopram 40mg (daily)
CUR_ILL: I had a minor muscle spasm on my shoulder from trapping cats
HISTORY: I previously had endometriosis but had a full hysterectomy and have been fine for 2 years

SYMPTOM_TEXT: MYOCARDITIS.  Patient is a 16 year old boy with ADHD who presented with fever and myalgias for 3 days, that progressed to sharp parasternal chest pain and some SOB. Patient received second dose Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine on 4/26, and after that shot experienced fever to 102 at home and myalgias. Subsequently his symptoms of chest pain have occurred. He underwent workup revealing of elevated Troponin, and EKG with some ST segment elevation, a slightly elevated CRP at 32, and a normal ECHO. Admitted for observation and concern for infectious myocarditis vs MIS-C. Cardiac MRI was done confirming Myocarditis, Troponin I was elevated and peaked at 23, 325pg/mL. Workup unrevealing of SARS. Other testing showed Resp virus panel negative, blood pcr for EBV, CMV, Parvovirus B19, enterovirus, and adenovirus all negative, HIV antigen/antibody testing negative. Patient treated with Ketorolac with steady improvement in symptoms over several hospital days. Discharged home 5/2 with Troponin I well down and symptoms resolved. Given reports in lay press regarding other cases of COVID-19 MRNA vaccine associated myocarditis, we are reporting this as a vaccine associated adverse event.

The left ventricular (LV) size is normal with normal LV wall                            thickness. The indexed LV end diastolic volume is 90 mL/m2. There is                        low normal systolic function of the LV with an ejection fraction of                        50%. There is late gadolinium enhancement involving 50-75% of the                          epicardial inferior and  inferolateral LV myocardium with increased T1                      and T2 signal.                                                                              2. The right ventricle is normal size with normal systolic function.                        3. Normal atrial size bilaterally.                                                          4. No evidence of significant valvular abnormalities.                                      5. Normal pericardium with no pericardial effusion.                                        Conclusion:                                                                                Epicardial late gadolinium enhancement present in the basal and mid                        lateral wall with elevated T1 and T2 values consistent with acute                          myocarditis.
CUR_ILL: None. This was second dose Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine given. No history COVID-19 disease.

She assured us she was fine and reiterated that this has happened before in the past anytime a needle was involved.  On 5/2/2021 she was contacted and she explained she looked a little pale throughout the day of vaccination, but feels fine now and just has a sore arm.

Since the 2nd vaccination date was so so close to the recurrence, I thought I should report it to VAERS.  I had some arm soreness  and mild "blahs" after both shots, but was basically OK.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am 67 years old and post-menopausal. On April 26, I began experiencing what looked like menstrual bleeding. There was no warning: no pain. No cramps. Very few clots. Flow was moderate, but lasted on and off until it stopped completely on May 1. I want to report this, because I have seen recent reports (just beginning) to emerge from credible sources that other post-menopausal women are experiencing this type of bleeding after being vaccinated. I am concerned, frightened, and trying to make an appointment to see my gynecologist. The flow and length of days involved pretty much mimicked the menstrual pattern I had before menopause. But I should not be bleeding at this age. This has never happened since I ceased menstruating at age 52 or 53. I think the CDC should know my story, here.

On April 6,2021 the patient received Covid IMZ 1 and had an anaphylactic reaction at the time immediately afterwards.  The complete details were not known until she returned on 04/27/21 to receive the 2nd IMZ for Covid. The patient listed on the CONSENT FORM that, she had ?allergies? to environmental things and did disclose this to the pharmacist, at the time. She had the ?back patch testing done? and had received allergy shots on a regular basis from a very young age for many years. The allergy testing resulted in her being allergic to weeds, grass, trees, all plants, bees, insects and more.  No medication allergies nor ingredient of medications allergies was noted, nor did pt note that she had ever had any issue with any IMZ in the past.        Pt received the 1st Covid IMZ on 04/06/21 at 8:02 am given by the Lead Tech CphT, she was immediately escorted to the waiting area? and stated that, ?within a minute she felt her throat closing up? and ?told the Health and Wellness associate?  - that was helping to sanitize the chairs for the day, that she didn?t feel good.  the associate immediately informed the pharmacist on duty . He went out to speak with the pt and had her sit on the floor and asked her to lye completely down on the floor.  The pt felt uncomfortable with this direction from the pharmacist and said she did not want to lye down, ---- as the floor was very dirty.  The pharmacist did not offer to get her a blanket, pillow nor did he ask any of the pharmacy associates to do so.  He also did not call the store management to assist with this ---- nor let them know she was having issues with the IMZ.  The patient said, ?she DID hold her hands up to her throat, and said she thought she was allergic to the vaccination? to the pharmacist---and he just returned to the pharmacy.  She ?thought? he was calling 911 or getting an epi-pen in case it needed to be administered. Pt stated that  returned to check on her after 15minutes, and then told her to set another 15 minutes and that her color looked better.  He seemed to think it was anxiety or a panic attack.  The patient stated that ?it was Not a panic attack? ?nor anxiety? at all.  She has taken Ativan since the age of 14 for other reasons, but she was not nervous about receiving the IMZ that day.        When the patient returned on 04/27/21, she informed the lead tech what had transpired on 04/06/21, and thought that it should be documented.  On 04/27/21, she was slightly apprehensive about receiving the IMZ, as she was worried it would happen again.  She was positive that she needed to complete the series and get the 2nd dose in spite of the concern.  I contacted the market director at the time and discussed the about events with her.  She said, ?it was OK to give it to her?, and to have the Epi-pen close by and have her under supervision at all times after the administration.       I gave her the 2nd IMZ on 04/27/21 at 9:31am and stayed by her side the entire time.  I had the epi-pen ?in ?hand" and the patient did say that her throat was scratchy and she became somewhat nervous, but as I continued to reassure her that I was there , and do matter what ?she would be OK?  and we would do whatever was necessary to be sure of that.  The patient had taken the Ativan on both 04/06/21 and 04/27/21 -- and it was not a panic attack nor anxiety as the pharmacist concluded or assumed on 04/06/21   The patient was upset on 04/27/21 that he had her sit on a dirty floor, did not come back to check on her except for 1 time -- and that was only to tell her to stay on the floor another 15 minutes.  She said, ?I don?t think he knows the protocol ?for a patient with an anaphylactic reaction??   She was very grateful  --- after waiting until she felt comfortable and steady to get up and go.  Before I administered the IMZ, I asked her, ?If she had anyone with her that was driving??  so, I?d know she was not alone in the store afterwards.       The patient did fine, and there was ?no need to administer? the Epi-Pen.  She was still concerned, ?that pharmacist did not know the proper protocol to follow for anaphylactic reactions??  She said, if he had been there on 04/27/2021, she was not going to have it done at that time.    I have statements from the administering technician and the associate that the patient first told ?she thought she was allergic? to the IMZ on 04/06/21.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 12 hours after injection, experienced normal side effects (e.g., muscle aches, chills, headache, fatigue)  Within 1 week of receiving the vaccine, I began to experience blurriness in my left eye.  After conferring with my primary care facility, it was recommended that I see an ophthalmologist. Confirmed that I had a Branch Retinal Vein Occlusion (BRVO) and recommended I meet with a retinal specialist.  Dr. confirmed the BRVO was caused by a blood clot and commenced treatment via eye injection.  I then met with my primary physician to discuss the situation.  He recommend further tests to determine whether I had other clotting.  In addition to blood work, he order MRIs of my brain, head and neck region and also recommended that I meet with a thrombosis specialist.  I met with a Dr. who ordered additional blood work for additional testing.  All tests performed to determine if I had additional clotting have come back negative.
LAB_DATA: As mentioned above, please consult my primary physician (and/or other physicians seen) for a read out of all blood work performed and results, as well as, for the dates/results from MRIs performed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: First dose: The evening after my first dose, around 9pm, my left foot quickly became very painful.  It felt like I had broken a bone in my foot, even tho that afternoon I had gone on a walk and had no issues at all until that evening.  The pain was so bad that I took ibuprofen and iced it, hoping to bring down swelling incase it was broken. There was no bruising, however.  I realized later that my foot looked a little distorted, like the muscles were all cramping. After a fitful night's sleep, I got up to go to the bathroom at 3am and the pain was almost gone and I could walk on the foot.  By morning, it wasn't even painful anymore.  I did not corelate this to the vaccination, but thought I had done something maybe on my walk earlier to cause it.  (I received the vaccine in my left arm, and this was my left foot) Second dose:  Within 2 hours of the vaccination, my left foot (same one) was in pain. It wasn't the same, didn't really feel like muscle cramping, and I would put weight on it. However, even with good arch supportive shoes that I wear to work every day, I had to take my shoes off to find any type of comfort.  My foot continued to hurt the rest of the night and into the 2nd day.  Even today (2 days later) my ankle still has a bit of pain, but isn't keeping me from normal events. I am in good shape typically, normal weight.  I definitely think this was a result of the vaccination. So I wanted to report it.
OTHER_MEDS: levothyroxine, biotin, vit d, calcium/magnesium, cortisol manager

As per employee report:  After my vaccine on 4/14/21 at designated vaccine site, I felt fine for the first 24 hours. At about the 24 hour mark my heart rate increased by about 20 bpm. I also started running a fever and my lymph nodes in my armpit was incredibly swollen. The following day, the fever was gone, but my heart rate was still high and every now and then jumping way up to 130ish bpm. That evening I went to bed and was awoken by my heart beating really fast and I monitored it on my Fitbit.. It raced up to about 170 bpm. At that point we made a trip to the ER.

Upper arm soreness started at about 8:30 pm, about 10 h after injection. Went to be like normal and arm was just sore, but nothing else at that time. At 1:10 am, patient woke up with horrible shakes, verging on convulsions, and the feeling of freezing to death. Uncontrollable shivers/shaking.  At around 1:40 am, patient was able to move enough to get out of bed to find a second blanket and extra strength Tylenol and took the Tylenol with some seltzer water and hid under blankets to get warmer. After about an hour, around 2:30 - 2:40 am, the shaking was reduced enough that the patient was able to relax and try to get to sleep. At 5;30 am, the patient woke up with much the same symptoms, but with the addition of the worst headache he had had since he stopped having migraines in his mid 20s and also his whole body ached like he had been hit by a truck (that [getting hit by a truck] had happened to him once about 15 years ago, so he has the actual reference to compare against).  This experience was worst overall body aches/pains ever experienced by the patient. He took additional Tylenol at 6 am and about 30 minutes later, the chills subsided and the pain was reduced enough that he could go to sleep again. Shortly before 10 am the symptoms started to get worse again and he took ibuprofen (400 mg) at 10 am, after the shakes started to come back. He has traded off every 4 hours taking tylenol and ibuprofen, which keeps the temperature perception swings to a minimum and overall body aches lower, but the headache does not go away. He feels exhausted, and has slept for spurts of 15 - 30 minutes on and off all day.  He was able to each crackers at around noon and some homemade chicken vegetable soup at about 1 pm as the nausea had subsided. Prior to that, he could only drink water and Gatorade. He is hoping that within 24 - 48 h he will feel much better, without having to take Tylenol or Ibuprofen.

He then lost consciousness and so I lifted his head to check for breathing and pulse which he had. I asked my technician to call 911, and asked my other tech to help me transition him to the floor so we can raise his legs to provide blood flow to his head. Mid-transition, he had a seizure. We brought him completely to the floor and just as I was about to turn him to his side, he regained consciousness. Pupils were dilated, breathing normal, pulse elevated. He also was able to speak immediately and confirmed feeling "okay". I then had my technician remain outside with him laying on the ground as I returned back inside the pharmacy to call management and my technician was still on the phone with EMS. I had the vaccine at 4:15 on March 30, 2021. Immediately I felt sharp pain in my arm. Then the Vertigo, which I had since day 7 of the first Moderna Vaccine, became very bad -- I was spinning and dizzy. I also immediately began sneezing, and that got worse over the next two hours, and sneezing, runny nose, sinus pain has not stopped (as I write this it is 2 days and five hours). I began running a fever the evening of May 1: my base line temperature is 96.9 - 97.6; it went up to 102.5. I took two Ibuprofen, some herbal remedies and aromatherapy and a cold towel on my face, and my temperature dropped within an hour to 99. The vertigo is better now, just happens for 30 seconds or so when I turn over, lay down or get up quickly. But my fever keeps going up, and my nose is running, ears feel clogged, and beginning to experience shortness of breath and some minor wheezing and cough. Mouth and sinuses very dry. Also, muscle aches everywhere, and having some trouble walking -- feel very stiff. Also, on March 30th, when I came home that evening, I experienced two strange neurological things: I hallucinated that a light was on -- I wondered why it was dim. Then it went off. When I checked the cord, it had not been plugged in at all: I only imagined it was on. Then, I went to make some tea, boiled water in the electric tea pot and heated something in the microwave. I went to pour the hot water but the tea pot was empty, but hot. I was very confused  -- where did all the water go? A minute or so later, I found a cup of tea with the tea bag and water in it: I had made the tea but blanked out and had no recollection of making it. In other words, I lost time and what ever happened in that time. Probably only a minute or two, but very strange. I can be a spacey person, but this was pretty extreme.
LAB_DATA: None (I did go to see Dr after the first vaccine when I got Vertigo and he did a basic neurological functioning test  -- everything looked OK. I also went to see a Neurologist-chiropractor, about the Vertigo after that first shot. He said my brain didn't seem too happy.) I have not talked to any doctor since these extreme symptoms began after the second one. If these symptoms continue I will call the Doctor tomorrow, which will be "Day 3"

First day: severe chills (extreme body shaking), and body temperature alternating between overheating and moderate/severe chills every several hours. Body fatigue, temperature varying from low 99 F up to 101.3 F. These symptoms subsided after about 2 days. Also developing during this time was an asthma attack, characterized by wheezing, coughing, and difficulty breathing. Patient has had life-long history of asthma, moderate, well-maintained with albuterol inhaler (life-long) and Qvar redihaler (beginning in early-mid 2020). However, after the common symptoms subsided, the asthma attack prolonged for over a week (2nd injection on 22 Apr 2021, and present as of reporting (03 May 2021). Albuterol inhaler would ease the wheezing, but no effect on mitigating the coughing / difficulty breathing. Qvar redihaler had no effect. Asthma attack would alternate in waves (approximately every hour up to 4-6 hour cycles), of breathing mostly clearly (some difficulty persisting), and severe attacks when extremely difficult to breathe.
LAB_DATA: Sought Urgent Care on 30 Apr 2021. Patient was refused entry to building after informing triage nurse of asthma symptoms, and was turned away due to fear of being contagious of covid-19. Was not physically screened, and was instead seen via tele-health, but no physical measurements / examinations were made. Patient was prescribed albuterol refill, and promethazine-dextromethorphan cough syrup. Albuterol inhaler helped to mitigate wheezing symptoms, but coughing / difficulty breathing still persisted. Promethazine was completely ineffective in mitigating any symptoms. ... Symptoms continued to worsen, and patient sought Emergency Department care on 01 May 2021. One hour prior to visiting hospital, patient was coughing severely and had extreme difficulty breathing. As the cough attacks would happen in waves, when the cough attack subsided enough, patient drove self to hospital while in able-body to drive before onset of next attack. At time of check-in at the Emergency Department, patient was unable to talk as talking triggered coughing attacks. Patient communicated with staff by written notes on smartphone. After check-in and triage, blood work was ordered as well as a chest x-ray. Both labs came back clear. Respiratory therapist administered albuterol/ipratropium (3mL, X1ED STA) nebulizer on 02 May @ 00:51, and patient was also administered Dexamethasone Sodium / Phasphate (could also be under the name Duonebs and IM Decadron) (10mg, X1ED STA) in right arm on 02 May @ 00:52, after nebulizer was complete. Breathing from these treatments had improved significantly, and patient was able to talk in complete sentences. Some coughing persisted, wheezing had mitigated, but was a significant improvement from intake when patient could not talk at all. Doctor reviewed labs and concluded that both chest x-ray and blood lab work showed no signs of other respiratory issues, and ruled out bronchitis/pneumonia, and was confident that patient's chief complaints were consistent with severe asthma exacerbation. According to lab reports: "Labs showed mild leukocytosis likely 2/2 stress demargination. CXR did not show PNA or other acute process. His presentation is most consistent w/ asthma exacerbation." Patient was discharged at around 02 May @ 02:00, and was sent with prescription for Tessalon pearles. Prednisone prescription was considered and discussed by doctor with patient, but was ultimately decided not to be prescribed by supervisory doctor (attending, I believe), to minimize possible interference between the prednisone and vaccine efficacy. ... Patient is now at home resting and recovering, taking prescribed medications. Patient was advised to monitor conditions over the next several days, and return to Emergency Department if symptoms do not improve within several more days after initial ED discharge.
OTHER_MEDS: Abilify, Lamictal, Albuterol inhaler, Qvar inhaler

The next day after my shot though, I woke up soaked in blood. I spent the next 7-8 hours going through 7 Super-size Tampax Tampons. It seemed like I was flash flooding blood  which was weird because ..well if my lining had just shed over the previous 7 days, where did all the blood come from? It ebbed within 24 hours and was back to normal the day after that before it ended.  Over by 2/12/21.  And now, it is 5/3/21 and I have not had a period since and have basically had early menopause jump in and get hot flashes every day! I read that its not actually menopause until our period has been gone for 6 months or more, and mine has really only been nearly 3, but I'm pretty sure I just got sterilized.  And I was a healthcare worker so I got it early, and I don't think the older people getting the shot in line before me would have been raising the concern about their menses cycles because they don't have them anymore.

ADVERSE EFFECT OF VACCINE; SHORTNESS OF BREATH; FATIGUE; HEADACHE; LOW PLATELETS; NIGHT SWEATS; DIAPHORESIS; BLURRED VISION; FEVER; BODY ACHES; This spontaneous report was received from a physician via a company representative and concerned a  white nonhispanic or Latino 50 year old male. Initial information was received on 28-APR-2021, with additional information obtained via telephone follow up from a physician on 29-APR-2021. The patient's height was 73 inches and weighed 252 lbs; approximate body mass index was 32.68 kg/m2. Medical history included: lung infection in 2014 which led to aortic valve disease which required biologic aortic valve replacement (2014); prolapse of right coronary aortic vale cusp, severe aortic insufficiency. There was no history of hyperlipidemia and was positive for family history of cardiovascular disease. Concurrent conditions included attention deficit disorder (ADD), back and neck problem, other congenital anomaly of heart, hypertension, lumbago, shortness of breath and thyroid nodule. The patient received COVID-19 vaccine Ad26.CoV2.S (suspension for injection, intramuscular, batch number and expiry date unknown) on 19-MAR-2021 for prophylactic vaccination. The batch number was not reported and has been requested. Concomitant medications included: carvedilol, losartan and atorvastatin (all for aortic valve replacement).  Also aspirin, Adderall (dextroamphetamine-amphetamine) both for unspecified indication. On 20-MAR-2021, the day after receiving the vaccine, the patient developed fevers, body aches and headache which resolved within 24 hours. Then a week on an unspecified date, he developed more symptoms which included fatigue, shortness of breath for the most part and some headaches. On 27-MAR-2021 the patient experienced a single episode of visual disturbance of burred vision while driving. At a stoplight vision in both eyes were blurred and he had trouble see the road; he no longer could drive. The blurred vision resolved within a few minutes and not vertigo or headache occurred at that time; and there were no other reported visual changes.  The patient visited his physician 28 days after receiving the vaccine on 16-APR-2021. He reported ongoing fatigue, body aches and headaches. No further visual changes or disturbances. He felt fatigue and shortness of breath were the most noticeable. He denied chest pains and fevers but has been experiencing night sweats (unspecified start date); and generally feels unwell and described himself as "feeling off". No leg edema or leg pain currently. Also no coughing, wheezing or bruising. His concentration was stable and there was no loss of memory. No other neurological symptoms. Physical exam was positive for chills diaphoresis, fatigue, fever and shortness of breath; cardiovascular examine revealed a murmur present, and pulmonary examine was normal breath sounds, no decreased breath sounds, wheezing, rhonchi or rates. Vital signs: blood pressure 104/68, pulse 93, temperature 98. The physician's assessment also included an adverse effect of vaccine. Laboratory results form 16-APR-2021 included: Creatinine (normal range 0.50 - 130 mg/dl) 1.09, white blood count (WBC) (normal range 3.8 - 10.8) 3.4, red blood cell count (RBC) (normal range 4.20 -5.8) 4.92, hemoglobin (normal range 13.2-17.1 g/DL) 13.9, glucose (normal range 71-99mg/dL)109, D-Dimer elevated at 286 (normal range <230), elevated C-Reactive Protein (CRP) (normal range 0 - 5 mg/L) 32.3, fibrinogen (results not reported), Covid-19 Antigen Antibody negative, platelet count 123,000 (lower limit of normal <140,000). The patient has a baseline platelet count of 200,000 from JAN-2021 and for the past 9 years had ranged from 180,000 - 240,000. A heparin-induced thrombocytopenia (HIT) was negative anti-PF4 antibody. On 20-APR-2021, the patient received Computerized tomogram (CT) of the head with and without contrast which was normal - no acute hemorrhage, mass effect or abnormal enhancement. The patient also had a CT chest with contrast with no evidence of pulmonary embolism to the segmental level; a 16 by 16 mm nodule with small calcification was noted, this was nonspecific but could reflect primary lung cancer, correlation with PET/CT is indicated. Additional laboratory results on 20-APR-2021 concerning serotonin release stated as follows: Positive, 6%, 40%, 37%. HIT panel negative with less than 0.6  antibody On 27-APR-2021 additional laboratory results were as follows: WBC 4.1, RBC 4.95, hemoglobin 14.0 g/dL, D-Dimer 275, fibrinogen 427 and HIT panel negative with less than 0.6  antibody. A hematologist was consulted and a complete blood count and HIT panel were performed on 28-APR-2021. Results were platelet count of 159,000, D Dimer of 275, HIT negative anti-PF4 antibody screen and the SRA assay was pending. On 29-APR-2021 the duplex of left lower extremity was negative for deep vein thrombosis (DVT). Additional laboratory reports included a platelet factor 4 antibody test test methodology which used latex particle enhanced immunoassay to detect anti -pF4/heparin antibodies (reference range 0.0-9), with the patient's value was <0.6 (negative). A COVID PCR test was not performed. An enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) test was ordered for 30-APR-2021 for anti-PF4 antibodies.  The action taken with COVID-19 vaccine Ad26.CoV2.S was not applicable. The outcome of the event blurred vision and fever were resolved;  the outcome of low platelets, adverse event of vaccine, shortness of breath, fatigue, headache, body aches, night sweats and diaphoresis were not reported. This report was serious (other medically important condition).; Sender's Comments: V0.20210456790-COVID-19 vaccine Ad26.CoV2.S -Low platelet counts,blurred vision,adverse affect of vaccination. 9pm 4/30 fatigue and aches set in. Mild symptoms.  Took a sleep aid and ibuprofen for bed. Fell asleep shortly after 10pm.   1am woke with intense chills, body aches and fever of 100.6.  Added heating pad, took Tylenol, added blankets and clothes but couldn?t get warm. Was so uncomfortable from the body aches I tossed and turned. I was extremely fatigued and weak.  Was still awake with extreme aches and chills at 4am, so I took a bath from 4-5am to warm up.  Symptoms persisted post-bath, but dozed off at 5:30am from exhaustion. Fever of 100.6 remained.  Rose at 8am feeling exhausted, heavy, brain fog, weak, chilled and body aches. Pins and needles over body from 1-9am.  Took 3 ibuprofen (600mg) and went back to bed. Fever reduced to 99, which was enough to break the chills/aches and allow rest. Slept until 10:30.  Chills and aches gone, but extreme fatigue and brain fog continued through day. Too weak to tend to kids, read books, or stand.  Appetite was fine. At dinner and snacks. Drank fluids and rotated ibuprofen and Tylenol as long as symptoms persisted.  Evening of 5/1 headache set in. Mostly dull ache.  Took OTC and went to bed.  Slept through the night, waking at 8am 5/2 with a smashing headache. It felt like someone hit me over the head with a bag of bricks, then put my head in a vice.  Drank water and took ibuprofen (400mg).  Still felt weak, but better.  As the day went on, symptoms improved and headache reduced. Went away completely in afternoon and back at bedtime.   Longest lasting symptoms of anyone I know. No health risks or complications. Generally healthy.

Two most recent crowns (One crown was about a year ago, the other was 5 months ago.) on two teeth on left side became very painful. Very similar to the same pain I experienced right after the crown was applied, with the exception that the pain would come and go. I would have no pain at all, then 5 minutes later the pain would increase to about a level 5. After about a half hour to an hour, the pain would subside.  This would repeat many times a day.   One week from the shot, I visited my dentist, but they didn't find any problems with the crowns. They gave me Amoxicillin thinking it may be an infection. I don't think it was because it was both of the teeth, one on top, one on the bottom at the exact same time. In the course of the next week the pain gradually subsided. Today it is almost completely gone and only on the most recent crown.
LAB_DATA: Xrays of teeth showed nothing wrong.

Approximately two days after receiving the second dose of the Moderna COVID 19 vaccine, I developed severe acute abdominal pain, and was diagnosed with an acute appendicitis requiring emergency surgery. After the surgery was completed, I was told that, based on clinical presentation, along with onset of symptoms, the infection was more advanced than would have been expected. After surgery, I developed an ileus, a systemic infection, as well as an abscess which required a drain to be placed in my pelvis. I was inpatient in the hospital for 9 days due to these complications, and it is my belief that there is not only a correlation between receiving the second dose of the vaccine and developing this appendicitis, but a causation. Though I have not seen any reported cases, I know that there were at least seven reported cases of appendicitis with the Pfizer variant, and the technologies are very similar.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Initially, my arm started throbbing in the afternoon of the first day.  Then I developed chills and started in the evening about 12 hours after my shot.  I went to bed.  When I woke up in the morning, I felt nauseous.  I got out of bed at about 8am to take 2 tylenol and shower hoping that I'd feel better.  While in the shower, I suddenly felt like I couldn't breathe and needed air.  The moments after that are bit hazy, but I can tell you somehow I found myself crashed into the window on the opposite wall of my bathroom.  Then I somehow made it out of my bathroom and somehow fell head first onto my carpeted floor of my bedroom.  I think I must have passed out for a minute.  Someone in my house heard me fall and came to help me back into bed and then I fell asleep in bed for the next 5 hours.  I woke feeling better, but not well.  I didn't feel considerably better until the next day.  My right arm still has not regained its strength completely.
LAB_DATA: None.  I did not see a doctor.  I would not have even reported it until a friend advised me to.  The reason my friend advised me to is because she shared that another friend of hers who had gotten the Pfizer 2nd shot passed out in her bathroom at 3 am.  She woke up covered in blood on her bathroom floor with 3 broken teeth and a broken nose.  I guess I am lucky, but there needs to be a better warning on the vaccine.
